$interpreted: Koll: Arooo...?
Kittyeyes: Oh, nothing serious happened, got totally rejected by Roger just now, that's all.
Kittyeyes: No big deal~
Kittyeyes: Koll, I'm so thankful I still have you by my side...
Kittyeyes: Can't keep sulking like this...
Kittyeyes: I'm going to go pick some flowers to decorate my room. Koll, you wanna come along?
Kittyeyes: What? You want me to stay here; you'll go pick the flowers for me?
Koll: Wooo~
Kittyeyes: Is that so...
Kittyeyes: Alright then, I'll take your word for it.
Kittyeyes: Guess I'll go clean up the room first; a change of scenery can't hurt.
Kittyeyes: Hmm, why are they gathering here?
Fearful Henchman: A-A-Are you  s-sure it's tonight?
Irritated Henchman: Yeah, when the time arrives, we'll take all the treasure from the camp. I'll then inform the Kingdom army to come get him.
Irritated Henchman: Maybe we c-c-can even get a portion of the bounty~
Kittyeyes: Why are you guys doing this!?
Fearful Henchman: B-B-Blame Roger. He beats us up for no reason these days. We've had enough of him for a while now!
Irritated Henchman: Also, we're the ones risking our lives robbing convoys, yet he gives away the goods we pillage all the time. We got stomachs to fill, ya know?
Kittyeyes: Then you can just leave; what's the point of informing the Kingdom army?
Fearful Henchman: Hmph, w-we need to do something to vent our frustration!
Irritated Henchman: No use blabbering to her. We'll capture her and use her as a hostage!
Irritated Henchman: Damnit, didn't think she would be such a hassle to deal with...
Fearful Henchman: W-What are we g-gonna do now?
Irritated Henchman: Grab Kittyeyes. Inform the others that there's a change of plans. Gotta leave now.
